notes.note:
In the online course, `University Chorus: Fundamentals of SingingÂ¿, students will receive instruction on the basics of solo and ensemble singing, such as breath, posture, tone production, basic pitch and rhythm reading, and vocal pedagogy. This online vocal training course focuses on introducing students to the fundamentals of singing and includes guest lectures on Alexander Technique, basic music-reading skills, and vocal training. Students will receive group and individual coaching on their vocal quality, tone production, breathing, and music-learning abilities, with a limited number of individual vocal coaching sessions per semester. No previous musical experience required. 

Contact Prof. Claudia Brown at cbrown34@buffalo.edu for more information.
The course for the Spring 2022 Semester is "Recording. Memory. Notation."
Please contact Prof. Melanie Aceto at aceto@buffalo.edu for permission to enroll.

catalog.title: Dance Accompaniment
catalog.description: Student musicians play for dance technique classes improvising a score in relationship to movement material. Students hone their improvisation skills and gain the skill and experience needed to play for dance companies and festivals throughout the world.

catalog.title: UB Symphony Orchestra
catalog.description: There are students from several different majors in our orchestra, and we encourage participation of everyone(regardless of their major) interested in playing some of the best music ever written. Eligible members of the orchestra will be invited to take instrumental lessons for free with the distinguished faculty of the UB Music Department.
